         MBK is headquartered in Jakarta, Indonesia, with close to 475 branches spread across 5 provinces (out of a total of 33 provinces), mainly in rural areas of Java Island. MBK employs over 4,300 people, of which 99 percent are women. The Company only serves low income rural women borrowers, which are underserved by banks. The Company will continue to expand its operations in rural and select urban areas of Indonesia.
